<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/76265455-carole"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1517067867i/76265455._UX100_CR0,13,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/76265455-carole">Carole</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Reading the first one again can be good but is not necessary. Barker wrote some reminders along the second novel, so you will not be lost. But it sure<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Reading the first one again can be good but is not necessary. Barker wrote some reminders along the second novel, so you will not be lost. But it sure is good to remember all the details of this incredible oniric world :D<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
