<div id="review_2615964906" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2615964906" />
    <a title="Jaycee  B" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/75765328-jaycee-b"><img alt="Jaycee  B" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1547480279p2/75765328.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2615964906?book_show_action=true">Jun 02, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jaycee  B" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jaycee  B" href="/user/show/75765328-jaycee-b">Jaycee  B</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2615964906" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11756897100122558219">I first read this book when I was in fifth grade, and I can say that even as a reread it was still deliciously bizarre and fascinating as when I first read it. I you’re going to read it, be sure to get a version with the pictures because Clive Barker is a terrific artist and the pictures bring a spine tingling intrigue to the whole book. I was about to give this book three stars because Clive Barker hasn’t written another book since 2012 I believe with the third book absolute midnight, which bot</span>
  <span id="freeText11756897100122558219" style="display:none">I first read this book when I was in fifth grade, and I can say that even as a reread it was still deliciously bizarre and fascinating as when I first read it. I you’re going to read it, be sure to get a version with the pictures because Clive Barker is a terrific artist and the pictures bring a spine tingling intrigue to the whole book. I was about to give this book three stars because Clive Barker hasn’t written another book since 2012 I believe with the third book absolute midnight, which bothers me greatly, but I don’t regret reading it even though I will probably be 50 before I find out how this story ends! But that’s not everyone’s cup of tea and if you don’t want to get too attached to a story that you can only imagine the ending to then you may not want to read this series. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11756897100122558219" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


